      "learned": "Students learned that: (1) For INDEPENDENT events, P(A ∩ B) = P(A) × P(B); (2) For DEPENDENT events (sampling without replacement), P(A ∩ B) = P(A) × P(B|A), where P(B|A) is the conditional probability of B given A has already occurred — computed by adjusting the sample space after the first draw. Students learned to identify which formula applies by asking: 'Does the first outcome change the conditions for the second?' Key vocabulary: multiplication law, with replacement, without replacement, conditional probability (informal), dependent events.",
